            <title>Feedback Loops in System Diagrams</title>
            
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Let's practice identifying feedback loops in a few more models. For each stock-flow model below, 
                    work in your group to
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Label each dependency link with a <q><m>+</m></q> or <q><m>-</m></q>, depending on how you think the stock impacts the flow rate.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Label each feedback loop as <q>amplifying</q> or <q>stabilizing</q>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Use the interactive as needed if it is helpful to 
                    visualize what you are labeling.
